This article discusses the collaboration between the United States and Sweden on clean energy and climate change. Sweden is recognized as a global leader in deploying clean energy solutions, with a vision to become an economy with no net emissions of greenhouse gases by 2050. The United States, under President Obama, has also made significant investments in clean energy and has seen a decrease in energy-related emissions. The United States and Sweden are committed to taking action on climate change through cooperation in international forums and partnerships. They are also working to provide technical assistance and financing for energy projects, particularly in regions with limited access to power. The article highlights the Swedish-American Green Alliance (SAGA), which promotes public-private partnerships and knowledge exchange on clean energy and sustainable development between the two countries.